President Obama announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key administration posts. These include Patrick A. Corvington for CEO of the Corporation for National and Community Service, Daniel I. Gordon for Administrator for Federal Procurement Policy at the Office of Management and Budget, Pamela S. Hyde for Administrator of the Substance Abuse and Mental Health Services Administration at the Department of Health and Human Services, John H. Laub for Director of the National Institute of Justice at the Department of Justice, Ian Solomon for United States Executive Director of the International Bank for Reconstruction and Development, and Richard Sorian for Assistant Secretary for Public Affairs at the Department of Health and Human Services. Each nominee brings extensive experience and expertise to their respective positions.